<doc id="632632" wikidata="Q2910773" url="?curid=632632" title="Shimon Even">
<text>Shimon Even (; June 15, 1935 – May 1, 2004) was an Israeli computer science researcher. His main topics of interest included algorithms, graph theory and cryptography. He was a member of the Computer Science Department at the Technion since 1974. Shimon Even was the PhD advisor of Oded Goldreich, a prominent cryptographer.

==Books==
* &quot;Algorithmic Combinatorics&quot;, Macmillan, 1973.
* &quot;Graph Algorithms&quot;, Computer Science Press, 1979. .

== See also ==
* Oblivious transfer

==External links==
* Memorial page
* Bibliography on DBLP
* Prof. Even&#x27;s &quot;genealogy&quot; (PDF)</text><links>
